      "text": "Nietzsche, we   learn in his \"Will to Power,\"\n was interested in the   establishment of perspectives. It was part of \nhis   program to give us these repeatedly. And in trying   to analyze \njust what he meant by them, I came upon   reasons for relating his cult \nof perspectives to his   dartlike style. And it was in the explanation \nof this   that I came upon the term, \"Perspective by Incongruity,\" which\n I shall now try to make clear."
